<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-14849] some empty/invalid bounds aren&apos;t caught by SelectStatement</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14849</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Nonsensical clustering bounds like &quot;c &amp;gt;= 100 AND c &amp;lt; 100&quot; aren&apos;t converted to Slices.NONE like they should be. Although this seems to be completely benign, it is technically incorrect and complicates some testing since it can cause memtables and sstables to return different results for the same data for these bounds in some cases.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13194237">CASSANDRA-14849</key>
            <summary>some empty/invalid bounds aren&apos;t caught by SelectStatement</summary>
